---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Megan Lange">
  <p class="mono accent">$ cat about.md</p>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <h2>Bio</h2>
  <p>
    Product manager with a background in commerce platforms: the systems that handle everything
    from how something is priced to how a customer pays, when a subscription renews, and how
    regulatory compliance shapes what markets a business can operate in.
  </p>
  <p>
    Before Microsoft, I was Program Manager (later Senior Program Manager) at DatStat, Inc., a
    Seattle-based startup I joined as an intern in 2014 while finishing my B.S. in Informatics at
    the University of Washington. I was the engineering team's first PM, established their agile
    practices, and led the ground-up build of a new web product to streamline their legacy
    offerings. When DatStat was acquired in April 2018, I decided it was time for something new.
  </p>
  <p>
    I joined Microsoft in September 2018 as a Program Manager in the Commerce Ecosystem
    organization. For my first three years I owned modernizing the transactional email system
    for the commercial commerce team: I built a new service and drove the migration off
    Salesforce toward an internally-hosted platform, Azure Email Orchestrator. That team took
    the opportunity to become the Microsoft Email Orchestrator team, taking on the email
    charter for both consumer and commercial commerce and striving to become Microsoft's
    email service.
  </p>
  <p>
    Over roughly eight years I moved from program management into product management on the
    Consumer Commerce Platform team, taking on increasing scope from single-capability
    ownership to cross-cutting programs spanning multiple engineering pillars and business
    areas.
  </p>
  <p>
    My strengths lie in driving clarity through complexity: designing the forums that get the
    right people talking, facilitating alignment across cross-functional stakeholders, and
    translating ambiguous regulatory or business requirements into concrete engineering work.
  </p>

  <h2>Timeline</h2>
  <ul class="timeline">
    <li>
      <span class="mono dim">Sep 2023 &ndash; 2026</span>
      <span>
        <strong>Senior Product Manager, Xbox Consumer Commerce Platform</strong> at
        Microsoft. Cross-cutting product ownership across Consumer REM (regulatory: FinCrime,
        Order-to-Cash, CSV Compliance), CSV / gift-card strategy, Sub + Title bundle capability,
        Narada email &amp; notifications, Digital Attach, and Purchase Pod leadership. Promoted
        to Senior in September 2023 while on maternity leave.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="mono dim">Jun 2020 &ndash; Sep 2023</span>
      <span>
        <strong>Product Manager 2 (with in-band promotion in 2021)</strong> at Microsoft.
        Transitioned from program management into product management on the commerce platform,
        growing scope from single-capability ownership to cross-cutting programs.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="mono dim">Sep 2018 &ndash; Jun 2020</span>
      <span>
        <strong>Program Manager, Commerce Ecosystem</strong> at Microsoft. Owned the
        modernization of the transactional email system for the commercial commerce team:
        built a new service and drove the migration off Salesforce toward Azure Email
        Orchestrator, the internally-hosted platform that later became the Microsoft Email
        Orchestrator team.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="mono dim">2014 &ndash; 2018</span>
      <span>
        <strong>Program Manager &rarr; Senior Program Manager, DatStat, Inc.</strong>
        (acquired by SCI Solutions in April 2018). First program manager in the engineering
        department. Established agile engineering processes and introduced agile methodologies to
        the team. Led the creation of a new web-based product from the ground up to streamline the
        company's legacy offerings. Started as an intern in 2014 during university, became
        full-time Program Manager after graduation, promoted to Senior Program Manager in
        May 2017.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="mono dim">June 2015</span>
      <span>
        <strong>B.S. Informatics, University of Washington</strong>. Cum Laude, 3.65 GPA.
      </span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Honors</h2>
  <ul class="honors">
    <li>
      <strong>Named inventor on U.S. Patent 11,144,365</strong>
      <span class="mono dim">(2021, filed May 29, 2020)</span>
      <p>
        "Automatic Clustering of Users for Enabling Viral Adoption of Applications Hosted by
        Multi-Tenant Systems" (USPTO application 16/888,645). Co-inventors: Ariel Gordon and
        Balu Chenicheri. Rare for a PM discipline.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Shipping team on Xbox-branded ROG Ally devices</strong>
      <span class="mono dim">(2025)</span>
      <p>Part of the broader team that shipped Microsoft's handheld gaming partnership with ASUS.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Shipping team on Lotus (Xbox Game Pass tier restructure)</strong>
      <span class="mono dim">(2025)</span>
      <p>
        Part of the broader team that shipped the Xbox Game Pass subscription pricing and tier
        changes.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>GTA VI launch on Xbox via Sub + Title</strong>
      <span class="mono dim">(2026)</span>
      <p>
        Launched GTA VI on Xbox using the Sub + Title bundle capability I originally built,
        bringing Xbox's offering to competitive parity with PlayStation and other platforms on
        that title.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Promoted to Senior Product Manager, Microsoft</strong>
      <span class="mono dim">(September 2023)</span>
      <p>
        Third promotion at Microsoft (Program Manager &rarr; PM2 in June 2020 &rarr; in-band
        promotion in 2021 &rarr; Senior in September 2023). Promotion came through while I was
        on maternity leave.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Senior Program Manager promotion, DatStat, Inc.</strong>
      <span class="mono dim">(May 2017)</span>
      <p>
        Promoted from Program Manager after establishing agile engineering practices and leading
        the ground-up build of a new web product to streamline the company's legacy offerings.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Cum Laude, B.S. Informatics, University of Washington</strong>
      <span class="mono dim">(June 2015, 3.65 GPA)</span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Interests</h2>
  <h3>Professionally</h3>
  <p>
    Gaming as an industry. The hard problems that come with working on platforms, not just
    services. AI tooling and skilling. Mostly, I love PMing: I love shipping, and I love
    bringing the people around me along for the ride.
  </p>
  <h3>Personally</h3>
  <p>
    Gaming. TV. Knitting, pottery, painting, and currently learning to sew. I also suffer from
    unwarranted confidence that I can absolutely install my own floors or build my own patio.
    Camping and snowboarding. And learning ASL and about Deaf community and culture, since
    my son is deaf.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  ul.timeline {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  ul.timeline li {
    padding: var(--space-md) 0;
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  ul.timeline li:last-child {
    border-bottom: 0;
  }
  ul.timeline .mono {
    min-width: 120px;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
  }
  ul.timeline strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  ul.honors {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  ul.honors > li {
    padding: var(--space-md) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  ul.honors > li:last-child {
    border-bottom: 0;
  }
  ul.honors strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-right: var(--space-sm);
  }
  ul.honors p {
    margin: var(--space-sm) 0 0;
  }
</style>
